**Event Title**: COM - Briefs Community

**Website**: [saintcon.org/com-briefs-community](https://saintcon.org/com-briefs-community)

**Description**: 
- Focuses on a variety of security topics in a community format.
- Includes short talks, termed "Briefs," lasting 10 minutes or less.
- Allows presenters to share experiences, successes, failures, and lessons learned in a casual environment.

**Presentations**:
- Participants can present on any topic of interest.
- Sign-up to present can be done through [this link](https://forms.gle/76Ex5bDKfhoic4RE9).

**Schedule**:
- **Hours of Operation**: 
  - Monday: Expo Closed
  - Tuesday to Thursday: Presentations during lunch
  - Friday: No Briefs

**MiniBadge**:
- Available at the community.
- Potential special minibadge for presenters.

**Images**:
- Event graphic logos available.
- Desktop wallpaper for download.

**Social Media & Support**:
- Community communication via Discord.
- Various support contacts listed for attendees, registrations, and sponsors.

**Notable Communities**: 
- AI, AppSec, BadgeLife, Blueteam, Hardware Hacking, Healthcare Hacking, IoT, LockPick, RFID/NFC, Space, and more.

**Events**: 
- Includes Application Security Jeopardy, Job Fair, LAN Party, and more.

**Organizers**: 
- Brought to you by G0vn4571 and Sheeprock.

**Note**: Participants are encouraged to engage, discuss, and explore various topics in a supportive and collaborative environment.